				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">He is right and he is wrong.
<br />

<br />
The lv 62 water pet has the ability to assinate, that is doing extremely large damage to a mos (32k or something close). There is only two things he is missing: It has to be an attack from behind and if I remember correctly, it doesn't work unless the mob is lv 46 or lower (possibly also humanoid).
<br />

<br />
The water pet is a poor tank against high level mobs and only works really well if you can place it for backstabs and when it doesn't tank. It can enrage like the other PoP pets and while enraging is immune against melee damage from the front. A pet can tank anything when enraged, but is very likely to die from some spell damage.
<br />

