<br />

<br />
They really can't fill the role of a MT at a level comparable to the player. They take damage at a much higher rate than a hybrid or a warrior against the same mob (meaning much higher healing costs). They can't hold aggro with any PC in melee range. They can't use skills to adjust their melee or taunting. They can't position a mob with any reliability. The list goes on.
<br />

<br />
Its sort of like saying that a Time-geared mage can fill the role of a tank at level 50. True, but...
<br />

<br />
For that matter, we recently had a Wizard as the "MT" backed up by a very dedicated Cleric that prevented a wipe against a PoTime mini. I wouldn't say that means "Wizards can fill the role of a MT in PoTime."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
