				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To answer the question of why water over air...
<br />

<br />
Post 50 Water pets are rogues. They have crap for HP and AC. I've heard it said that post 50's Air pets are modeled after monks, but I don't buy it. I've never seen any kind of monk type moves out of my Air pets. They behave like warrior class to me. They have way better HP and AC than Water.
<br />

<br />
At the time that I first told the Necro and Druid you speak of about that 32k BS. I didn't know that it was level 45 or below so I couldn't have told them. I didn't find this out until weeks later when chatting with a 65 mage that was doing a parchment turn in for me. If I had known, I would've told them. I did however say it was an assasinate so they must have misunderstood if they told you I said it procced.
<br />

<br />
As far as fulfilling the role of MT. It's capable of taking enough damage that if the mobs are slowed a cleric can keep it healed. The cleric I play with says that my Air pet is easier to heal than a lot of tanks he's played with, but we all know a lot of tanks out there need better gear too  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Give me a real tank up front any day for precisely the reasons that itchyban stated, but if there isn't a tank available and I've got a slower and a healer sitting there you can bet I'll pull one for Jobober and more than likely he'll still be floating there waiting on me to pull another...
<br />

<br />
As far as whining that our pets need improvement. I'm a brand new 65 Mage. The pets I have right now in comparison to the one's I've lived with in lower levels are awesome. Give me more time and experience and I'm sure I'll run across lots of things that I want to do and can't because of pet limitations. So to me, they're great... to a Time geared mage with 300 AA's... probably not so great anymore...<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/groovehead/poddy.jpg"><b>
<br />
